Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.34,0:00:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and Gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.59,0:00:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, for your pleasure, we present to you, \Na Christmas tale with a tint of drama: {/a little bit sad}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.72,0:00:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"Jeremy's Tree."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.72,0:00:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear grandfathers, grandmothers, \Npapas, mamas, and, of course children!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.35,0:00:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Even those who came on their own\Nare welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.48,0:00:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, well, let's get started now!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.69,0:00:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.24,0:00:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.87,0:01:12.42,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(900,200)\c&HFAFEFD&\bord0.1\blur5\b0\fnEraser\fs50\pos(263.333,60)\3c&H353B6B&} Jeremy's Tree
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.97,0:01:18.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(200,200)\b0\fs30\c&HFFFFFF&\blur5\bord0.5\3c&H1F2149&\pos(263.333,160)} Original work by Iruka {原作}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.06,0:01:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year, when December finally comes, \NI become by all means twitchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.40,0:01:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the Christmas month \Nis also my birthday month.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.57,0:01:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not even a Christian,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.70,0:01:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet, every Christmas eve{/day}, I offer a prayer \Nof gratitude for the happiness of being alive. {lit is "I am doing gratitude/thanks" and i've no clue what it means}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.62,0:01:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But also, I pray that we don't forget \Nthat there are countless people and creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.38,0:01:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,stricken with sadness, \Nunder this very same sky. {lit: I think we can't forget that there are many people and living beings thinking sad thoughts}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.59,0:02:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be nicer if everyone was happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.55,0:02:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This story you're about to see - Jeremy's tree \Nis the materialization of this pious wish of mine. {lit: jeremy's tree is a story I made by putting in that wish}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.42,0:02:36.76,Song,,0,0,0,,Powdered snow is falling on the flowers in the field {couldn't find any lyrics for this one so basing this solely around the wisper's output}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.63,0:02:45.47,Song,,0,0,0,,Let's go play around together, \Nbecause it's a wonderful Christmas eve, Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.14,0:02:48.94,Song,,0,0,0,,Wave your hand, Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:57.53,Song,,0,0,0,,When you break into a run, \Nthe morning sun glitters on your hair
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:05.87,Song,,0,0,0,,All the time, I keep hearing it -
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.79,0:03:13.79,Song,,0,0,0,,Mama's voice from the long-long past
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.79,0:03:16.76,Song,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, hold your head high {to throw out one's chest; to be puffed up with pride - could be it's what he hears mom's voice saying, then it's probably something less extreme and boastful, like simple "straighten your back"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.17,0:03:18.67,Song,,0,0,0,,Jeremy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.09,0:03:21.05,Song,,0,0,0,,with a smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.05,0:03:26.26,Song,,0,0,0,,Wherever you go, hit it with a bouncy step
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.48,0:03:35.73,Song,,0,0,0,,Keep going always straight ahead, \Nwithout ever looking back
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:42.61,Song,,0,0,0,,However, if you see someone crying, \Nthere's no shame doing that {/in looking back}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.61,0:03:46.24,Song,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, hold your head high
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:47.91,Song,,0,0,0,,Jeremy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.33,0:03:50.08,Song,,0,0,0,,with a smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:55.67,Song,,0,0,0,,Wherever you go, hit it with a bouncy step
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.63,0:04:01.09,Song,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)} Wherever you go, bouncy step...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.38,0:04:04.47,Song,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)} Wherever you go, bouncy step...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:09.47,Song,,0,0,0,,Wherever you go, walk with a bouncy step...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.46,0:04:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,A wizard's Christmas cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.63,0:04:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.67,0:04:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing with that cake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.39,0:04:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.58,0:05:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,After I shook it up like this,\NI can no longer return it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.60,0:05:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, guys! Anyone's hungry here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.07,0:05:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Bon appetit!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.70,0:05:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's start the Christmas party!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.54,0:05:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.22,0:06:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor thing. He's chilled to the marrow. {he uses "boku" later}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.82,0:06:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.32,0:06:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.78,0:06:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, tell me, where'd you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here flying from a faraway forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.29,0:06:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,From the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.42,0:06:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here to find the fir tree \Nthat I spent my whole life with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.96,0:06:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The fir tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.09,0:06:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Deep inside the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.89,0:06:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,spreading out its green branches \Nin all directions,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.01,0:06:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it is ever so gently \Nwatching over all of us, the fir tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.85,0:07:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, it was like a mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.48,0:07:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Back when I was little, I suddenly found myself \Nall alone in the nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.07,0:07:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But despite that, \NI've not been feeling one bit lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.75,0:08:15.64,Song,,0,0,0,,Felled in the forest, fir tree {woohoo, I found lyrics: https://ameblo.jp/yurara887/entry-12224599054.html} {切りたおされた　樅の木よ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.64,0:08:23.23,Song,,0,0,0,,The silver stars are an illusion {/but a beautiful lie } {no clue what this means: 銀の星は　まがいもの}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.98,0:08:31.70,Song,,0,0,0,,They don't suit you, not one bit {おまえには　似合わない}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.70,0:08:37.74,Song,,0,0,0,,But they do suit me... {私が似合う - no clue again, could be "but I suit you/them"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.00,0:08:43.29,Song,,0,0,0,,Standing still,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.87,0:08:47.29,Song,,0,0,0,,my fir tree, ah... {立ちつくす　樅の木よ}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.29,0:08:55.01,Song,,0,0,0,,Tell me, do you still remember it - that forest? {憶えているか　あの森を}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.01,0:09:06.86,Song,,0,0,0,,Where me and you slept away those long dark nights... {黒い夜には　私と眠った}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.42,0:09:37.39,Song,,0,0,0,,Felled in the forest, fir tree {it's no longer technically in the forest but w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.47,0:09:45.44,Song,,0,0,0,,At last, I came to meet with you {私はやって来た}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.44,0:09:52.86,Song,,0,0,0,,I'll follow you, my beloved dear, {いとおしい　おまえのため}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.94,0:09:59.82,Song,,0,0,0,,Even in the hereafter {hades; realm of the dead; the next world​} {黄泉の国までも} {/Even into the next world }
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.58,0:10:08.92,Song,,0,0,0,,Come back to life, my fir tree! {よみがえれ　樅の木よ}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.46,0:10:15.72,Song,,0,0,0,,Your branches are still in the prime of youth {おまえの枝は　わかざかり}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.34,0:10:28.06,Song,,0,0,0,,While the flames keep blinking... {炎がまばたき　する間に}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.95,0:10:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping to return home \Nat least a single branch of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.87,0:10:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to live once more \Ntogether with it in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.08,0:10:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure is one heartbreaking story.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.21,0:10:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The fir tree that you so cherished, \Nchopped off like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.97,0:10:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I know what to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll both look for that precious fir tree of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.18,0:11:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.24,0:11:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Is that your tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.41,0:11:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.29,0:11:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one? Is this the tree we're looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.97,0:11:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem to be this fir either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.89,0:11:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's one luxurious mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.73,0:11:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet they've got a splendiferous \NChristmas tree too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.49,0:12:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.36,0:12:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my first time seeing a party that dazzling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.83,0:12:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! There's the fir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This looks similar to my forest's fir...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.96,0:12:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Try calling it. {/crying/singing/tweeting}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.12,0:12:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the fir you're looking for, \Nit'll surely react!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.14,0:12:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.14,0:12:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the fir from my forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.90,0:12:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.19,0:12:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go ask if we can have \Nat least one branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.57,0:12:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there's a small bird, \Nwho needs that fir tree you got... {/who was looking for }
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.24,0:12:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.08,0:12:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Tightwads! {/you stingy}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.08,0:12:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Like small kids! {has to be "赤ん坊" or "baby; infant" but I don't see what it may mean here}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.06,0:13:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe if I try asking once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.77,0:13:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,After we went through all this trouble... {lit: after all, we managed to meet with it at last}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.28,0:13:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... The lights are out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.57,0:13:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do, Jeremy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.12,0:13:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing what Santa Claus does. {/imitate}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.04,0:13:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Except that the chimney is not an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.84,0:13:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.13,0:13:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like they forgot to lock it. {lit is "turn the key" but I don't suppose you'd lock a window with a key}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.05,0:13:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our fir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.79,0:14:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A branch!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.13,0:14:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The fir gifted you one of its twigs. {/small branch}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.76,0:14:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Christmas tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.09,0:14:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.72,0:14:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Rats!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.93,0:14:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.80,0:15:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.97,0:15:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay strong, Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.89,0:15:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.89,0:15:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, you can't die here!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.67,0:15:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.17,0:15:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You silly thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.84,0:15:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I be dying?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.59,0:15:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.85,0:15:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was for me that you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.60,0:15:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.22,0:16:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you got to meet that fir,\Nit's all that matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.81,0:16:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could go to the forest with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.07,0:16:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.49,0:16:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremy... Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Santa Claus!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.00,0:16:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Father Santa... {/grandpa}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.51,0:16:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I have this fir twig... {no clue what he means to say: "I want/I have/etc" assumed he means to say "I want [to carry into the forest] this twig" as it is later}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I know all about that, Jeremy. {again, no clue what he understands}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.80,0:16:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,No need. No need to explain. {still no clue, could be "agreed, I will grant [your wish]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.52,0:16:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what should I present our Jeremy with?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.10,0:16:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to fly away \Nto carry this twig back to the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.11,0:16:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! Want to go to the forest, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.74,0:16:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid, splendid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.24,0:16:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly feel so drowsy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.37,0:17:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleep tight, Jeremy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.00,0:17:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time you open your eyes, \Nyou'll be in the forest already! {/wake up}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.69,0:17:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people are frolicking around, \Nlike powdery snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.16,0:17:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of that encounter on a city corner, {this lines seems to lead nowhere so as the next one, hence I'm artificially including some message/sense into it}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.45,0:17:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,between a small bird, looking for a fir tree \Nand a young boy, living all by himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.46,0:18:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,on that Christmas night, deep inside the forest, \Nthe boy settled down for an eternal sleep. {/fell asleep forever}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,After some winters passed, \Na fir tree had sprouted from that spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.31,0:18:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,gradually growing big and strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.11,0:18:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, a great many \Nof small birds have made pilgrimage to that place,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,where tenderly,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.50,0:18:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,tenderly, they sing it \Nthe sweetest lullaby ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.55,0:18:39.26,Song,,0,0,0,,Friends from the Beech Forest, {ブナの森の仲間たち}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.93,0:18:46.98,Song,,0,0,0,,Have you all gone to sleep already? {もうみんな眠りましたか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.52,0:18:54.23,Song,,0,0,0,,Tell me, o wise Grandfather Moss, {なんじゃもんじゃごけのおじいさん - no clue what's the hidden meaning behind addressing some specific moss for it and calling it by full name; the word "nanjamonjagoke" is one of those in japanese that sound just like that thing they denote - mushi so maybe it's some playful silly form of a tongue-twister for children? I suspect that this moss is already a part of some other japanese fairy tale/folklore; also this is technically "grandpa of moss" so could be some even higher being, like the yokai that created everything in the forest?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.90,0:19:02.28,Song,,0,0,0,,The sad story of love of Princess Nettle {悲しい恋をしたいらくさ姫の}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.28,0:19:08.71,Song,,0,0,0,,If only you know this old legend, \Nwill you tell it to me? {伝説 知っていますか？}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.46,0:19:19.09,Song,,0,0,0,,This is my favorite lullaby \Nbefore going to sleep {ぼくが大好きなおやすみ前の子守唄}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.57,0:19:47.33,Song,,0,0,0,,When I open my eyes, \Nit'll be a brand new day {目が覚めたら明日こそ} {/tomorrow}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.91,0:19:54.84,Song,,0,0,0,,Let's go to faraway towns, \Nmeet the people there {遠くの町の人々に}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.25,0:20:01.43,Song,,0,0,0,,Would they be happy \Nif we brought them a bouquet of herbs? {ハーブの花束届けましょう} {was "ハーヴ" originally but has to be ハーブ}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.05,0:20:09.60,Song,,0,0,0,,Maybe the thorns in their hearts would then peel away {心の棘がぬける様に}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.60,0:20:15.90,Song,,0,0,0,,From somewhere, I hear the ringing of sheep bells {どこかで聞こえるひつじの鈴の音}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:26.08,Song,,0,0,0,,Even the wind had already fallen asleep - \Nsee you tomorrow {/until tomorrow} {風も眠ってしまったから 又あした}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.33,0:20:37.21,Song,,0,0,0,,As the moonlight blankets me gently, I will sleep. {月の光をあびながら眠ります}
